```
location /api/ {
    proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000/;
    # ...other settings...
}
```
This strips /api from the path. So /api/tts → /tts.

**Solution:**  
Change your nginx config to:
```
location /api/ {
    proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/;
    # ...other settings...
}
```
This will preserve the /api prefix.

**Steps:**
1. Edit your nginx config (usually `/etc/nginx/sites-available/default` or similar).
2. In the `location /api/` block, set:
   ```
   proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:8000/api/;
   ```
3. Reload nginx:
   ```
   systemctl reload nginx
   ```
4. Test your endpoint again.

